quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Variables[/h1]

Examples of variable declarations:[code format="java" codeId="718"]class MyClass {
  public static void main(String[ ] args) {
    [b]String[/b] name ="David";
    [b]int[/b] age = 42;
    [b]double [/b]score =15.9;
    [b]char[/b] group = 'Z';
  }
}[/code]
[b]char [/b]stands for character and holds a single character.

Another type is the [b]Boolean [/b]type, which has only two possible values: [b]true [/b]and [b]false[/b].
This data type is used for simple flags that track true/false conditions.
[b]For example:[/b] [code format="java" ][b]boolean [/b]online = true;[/code]
[note]You can use a comma-separated list to declare more than one variable of the specified type. Example: int a = 42, b = 11;[/note]
